cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Spaghetti Architect or its benchmark, please cite it as below."
title: "Spaghetti Architect: an anti-optimization transpiler and a ground-truth, contamination-resistant LLM code benchmark"
abstract: >-
  Spaghetti Architect maps a clean JSON intermediate representation to deliberately
  redundant, fully-flattened, yet provably-correct code in Python, JavaScript, Go,
  Java and C++, gated by an oracle validator. On top of it, a benchmark generator
  produces ground-truth, tunable, contamination-resistant code tasks (refactoring,
  LLM-as-judge quality, and comprehension) with two orthogonal difficulty axes:
  intrinsic complexity (problem size) and incidental complexity (presentation mess
  at fixed semantics).
type: software
version: "0.2.0"
date-released: "2026-06-21"
license: "MIT"
repository-code: "https://github.com/KurathSec/Spaghetti-Architect"
